A 25-year-old man,  James Isaac, has been dragged before an Ota, Ogun State Magistrates’ Court for allegedly stealing an unregistered motorcycle valued at N360,000. Isaac of no fixed address, is facing a charge of stealing, an offence he denied committing. The prosecutor, Sergeant Chudu Gbesi, told the court that the accused committed the alleged offence in Ota, sometime in January. Gbesi said that the accused was caught by security guards while he was about to steal the unregistered motorcycle where it was parked. The prosecutor said that the offence contravened the provisions of Section 319(9) of the Criminal Code, Laws of Ogun State, 2006. The Senior Magistrate, Mr. G. E. Akan, granted the accused bail in the sum of N200,000 with two suretie. 